snippet: The charred carcass of one of Queen Elizabeth’s own swans was found after having been barbecued and eaten, according to the police and a charity called Swan Lifeline.
abstract: Charred carcass of one of Queen Elizabeth’s own swans is found on a riverbank near Windsor Castle after having been barbecued and eaten; wild swans are also protected under a 1981 act, and to injure or kill a swan, let alone eat one, is against the law.
